1. Decimal Number System (Base 10):
Uses digits: 0–9
Base = 10
2. Binary Number System (Base 2):
Uses digits: 0 and 1
Base = 2
Used in computers
3. Octal Number System (Base 8):
Uses digits: 0–7
Base = 8
4. Hexadecimal Number System (Base 16):
Uses digits: 0–9 and A–F
A = 10, B = 11, … F = 15
Base = 16
